item.title: Ultimate Loyalty: Japanese Dog Refuses to Leave Injured Friend Behind
item.description:
Ultimate Loyalty: Japanese Dog Refuses to Leave Injured Friend Behind
http://www.facebook.com/lifewithdogs: Emerging coverage from Japan offers a moving example of ultimate dog loyalty, and clearly illustrates the challenges faced by animal victims of the earthquake and tsunami. The dogs were picked up after the video was filmed, and are in the care of a local shelter. Updates and pics will be here in the coming days: http://www.facebook.com/lifewithdogs Translation of conversation in video: We are in Arahama area. Looks like there is a dog. There is a dog. He looks tired and dirty. He must have been caught in the tsunami. He looks very dirty. He has a collar. He must be someone's pet. He has a silver collar. He is shaking. He seems very afraid. Oh, there is another dog. I wonder if he is dead. Where? Right there. There is another dog right next to the one sitting down. He is not moving. I wonder. I wonder if he is alright. The dog is protecting him. Yes. He is protecting the dog. That is why he did not want us to approach them. He was trying to keep us at bay. I can't watch this. This is a very difficult to watch. Oh. Look. He is moving. He is alive. I am so happy to see that he is alive. Yes! Yes! He is alive. He looks to be weakened. We need to them to be rescued soon. We really want them rescued soon. Oh good. He's getting up. It is amazing how they survived the tremendous earthquake and tsunami. It's just amazing that they survived through this all. Want to donate? http://www.worldvets.org http://www.facebook.com/pages/Japan-Earthquake-Animal-Rescue-and-Support/207835229228979 (partnering with World Vets for relief efforts) Our main site server is down at www.lifewithdogs.tv until Friday thanks to an unforeseen traffic ramp-up. Please visit our facebook page in the interim for news.

item.title: Rebecca Black: The next Justin Bieber or just a joke?
item.description:
Rebecca Black: The next Justin Bieber or just a joke?
http://Facebook.com/ClevverTV - Become a Fan! http://Twitter.com/ClevverTV - Follow Us! Watch "Friday" music video: http://youtu.be/CD2LRROpph0?hd=1 Rebecca Black has everyone and their mother talking about her new music video "Friday." Is she really worthy of being compared to Justin Bieber? Full report coming up in our next ClevverTV segment. Hey ClevverTV peeps, what's goin on, I'm Joslyn Davis in the Hollywood studio today. You might have noticed there's a girl named Rebecca Black that's been getting an awful lot of buzz this week. Her music video "Friday" hit YouTube last Friday, and has already racked up almost 6 million hits. Now people are even comparing her to gasp! Justin Bieber!! While some are loving the new jam about the kickoff of the weekend, others are slamming Rebecca, accusing her video of being a parody. The video's gotten so much buzz that YouTube users have even begun creating response videos, one of which changes the lyrics from "Friday" to "Fried Eggs." So who is this Rebecca Black character? All we know is she recorded the fun vid with L.A.-based Ark Music Factory. While it only had 4000 views on Friday, that number started skyrocketing over the weekend and into this week, making her the latest YouTube sensation. Justin Bieber status? That's for you to decide. So comment below, and remember to click subscribe on our channel for more stories like this one. I'm Joslyn Davis from the ClevverTV studios, saying bye for now.
